		<br>
		<hr>
		<a name="documentation"></a>
		<h1>Documentation<a href="#top">(back to top)</a></h1>
		<br>
		Feel free to directly link (hotlink) to the images with your website or app.<br>
		<br>
		The images are hosted on a dedicated server with a gigabit connection and tons of bandwidth.<br>
		<br>
		<br>
		<h1>Card Images</h1>
		<p>Most card images are in 480x680 resolution and come from <a href="http://www.slightlymagic.net/forum/viewforum.php?f=15">CCGHQ</a>.<br>
		<br>
		Lower resolution images are provided until a higher resolution is available.<br>
		<br>
		Reference the <a href="#setList">set list</a> table to see which resolution each set is currently in.<br>
		<br>
		Some cards may be in a different resolution, such as the 'plane' cards in the Planechase sets.<br>
		<br>
		URLs are case insensitive and multiple naming formats are supported:
		<ul>
			<li>Card Names&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Supported</li>
			<li><a href="http://mtgjson.com">MTGJSON</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Supported</li>
			<li><a href="http://www.woogerworks.com/">Cockatrice</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Supported</li>
			<li><a href="http://www.slightlymagic.net/forum/viewforum.php?f=15">CCGHQ</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Supported</li>
		</ul>
		<br>
		<br>
		Images are available via <strong>3</strong> different methods:<br>
		<br>
		</p>
		<div class="code">
			<h2>Access By Set</h2>
			<br>
			<strong>Format</strong>: http://mtgimage.com/set/&lt;set code&gt;/&lt;card name&gt;.jpg<br>
			<br>
			or<br>
			<br>
			<strong>Format</strong>: http://mtgimage.com/setname/&lt;set name&gt;/&lt;card name&gt;.jpg<br>
			<br>
			<br>
			<strong>Examples</strong>:<br>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/set/ARB/Sen Triplets.jpg">Sen Triplets</a> &nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/set/ARB/Sen Triplets.jpg</li>
				<li><a href="/set/RTR/Archweaver.full.jpg">Archweaver</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/set/RTR/Archweaver.full.jpg</li>
				<li><a href="/setname/Zendikar/Harrow.jpg">Harrow</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/setname/Zendikar/Harrow.jpg</li>
			</ul>
			<br>
			<p>
			You can browse the set images via <a href="/set/">set code</a> or <a href="/setname/">set name</a><br>
			<br>
			Even though when browsing names are lowercase, you can access them with different cases/formats.<br>
			</p>
		</div>
		<br>
		<br>
		<div class="code">
			<h2>Access By Card</h2>
			<br>
			<strong>Format</strong>: http://mtgimage.com/card/&lt;card name&gt;.jpg<br>
			<br>
			<strong>Examples</strong>:<br>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/card/Craw Wurm.jpg">Craw Wurm</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/card/Craw Wurm.jpg</li>
				<li><a href="/card/Serra_Angel.jpg">Serra Angel</a> &nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/card/Serra_Angel.jpg</li>
			</ul>
			<br>
			<p>The card used comes from the latest set it was printed in, unless an earlier set has a higher resolution.<br>
			<br>
			Token images are not available this way. You need to access those by set/setname.<br>
			</p>
		</div>
		<br>
		<br>
		<div class="code">
			<h2>Access By multiverseid</h2>
			<br>
			<strong>Format</strong>: http://mtgimage.com/multiverseid/&lt;multiverseid&gt;.jpg<br>
			<br>
			<strong>Examples</strong>:<br>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/multiverseid/174859.jpg">Elspeth, Knight-Errant</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/multiverseid/174859.jpg</li>
				<li><a href="/multiverseid/279712.jpg">Akroma's Memorial</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/multiverseid/279712.jpg</li>
			</ul>
			</p>
		</div>
		<br>
		<br>
		<hr>
		<h1>Crops</h1>
		For artwork crops instead of full cards, change the image name to end with '-crop.jpg' or '.crop.jpg' instead of '.jpg'<br>
		<br>
		Like cards, crops are slightly compressed. For uncompressed crops the image name should end with '.crop.hq.jpg'<br>
		<br>
		Crops have various resolutions.<br>
		<br>
		<br>
		<hr>
		<h1>Split Cards</h1>
		Split cards like 'Fire // Ice' can be accessed in multiple ways:<br>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="/set/DDJ/fireice.jpg">fireice.jpg</a></li>
			<li><a href="/set/DDJ/fire ice.jpg">fire ice.jpg</a></li>
			<li><a href="/set/DDJ/fire.jpg">fire.jpg</a></li>
			<li><a href="/set/DDJ/ice.jpg">ice.jpg</a></li>
		</ul>
		<br>
		<hr>
		<a name="imageCompression"></a>
		<h1>Image Compression</h1>
		The card images have been compressed a bit to save on bandwidth.<br>
		<br>
		If you want to access the full quality, uncompressed image, change the image name to end with '.hq.jpg' instead of '.jpg'<br>
		<br>
		Note: There is very little visual difference between the two.<br>
		<br>
		Example <a href="/set/M14/Chandra's Phoenix.jpg">Chandra's Phoenix.jpg (95k)</a> vs <a href="/set/M14/Chandra's Phoenix.hq.jpg">Chandra's Phoenix.hq.jpg (471k)</a>
		<br>
		<br>
		<hr>
		<h1>Symbols<a href="#top">(back to top)</a></h1>
		<p>Symbols are available in several sizes and formats.<br>
		<br>
		<strong>Formats</strong>: PNG, GIF, SVG<br>
		<br>
		<strong>Sizes</strong>: {symbolSizes}<br>
		<br>
		Each size is the maximum width or height of the symbol image (eg 32x27 or 127x128).<br>
		<br>
		URLs are case insensitive.<br>
		</p>
		<br>
		<br>
		<div class="code">
			<h2>Set Symbols</h2>
			<p><br>
			<strong>Format</strong>: http://mtgimage.com/symbol/set/&lt;set code&gt;/&lt;rarity&gt;/&lt;size&gt;.&lt;format&gt;<br>
			<br>
			<strong>Examples</strong>:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/symbol/set/tor/r/64.gif">Torment Rare 64 GIF</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/set/tor/r/64.gif</li>
				<li><a href="/symbol/set/ths/m/128.png">Theros Mythic 128 PNG</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/set/ths/m/128.png</li>
				<li><a href="/symbol/set/ody/c/256.png">Odyssey Common 256 PNG</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/set/ody/c/256.png</li>
			</ul>
			<p><br>
			<strong>&nbsp;SVG Format</strong>: http://mtgimage.com/symbol/set/&lt;set code&gt;/&lt;rarity&gt;.svg<br>
			<strong>SVG Example</strong>: <a href="/symbol/set/ice/u.svg">Ice Age Uncommon SVG</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/set/ice/u.svg<br>
			<br>
			&lt;rarity&gt; is a single letter representing the rarity: c, u, r, m, s<br>
			You can also use the full rarity: common, uncommon, rare, mythic, special<br>
			<br>
			Use rarity 'c' for basic lands.<br>
			Use rarity 's' for Time Spiral "Timeshifted" cards (TSB) and Vanguard (VAN).<br>
			<br>
			The <a href="#setList">set list</a> denotes which rarities are available for which sets.<br>
			<br>
			Set symbols are rendered in 'accurate' style.<br>
			</p>
		</div>
		<br>
		<br>
		<div class="code symbolsSection" id="manaSymbolsSection">
			<h2>Mana Symbols</h2>
			<p><br>
			<strong>Format</strong>: http://mtgimage.com/symbol/mana/&lt;mana code&gt;/&lt;size&gt;.&lt;format&gt;<br>
			<br>
			<strong>Examples</strong>:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/symbol/mana/g/64.gif">Green 64 GIF</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/mana/g/64.gif</li>
				<li><a href="/symbol/mana/10/128.png">10 Colorless 128 PNG</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/mana/10/128.png</li>
				<li><a href="/symbol/mana/uw/256.png">Blue/White 256 PNG</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/mana/uw/256.png</li>
			</ul>
			<p><br>
			<strong>&nbsp;SVG Format</strong>: http://mtgimage.com/symbol/mana/&lt;mana code&gt;.svg<br>
			<strong>SVG Example</strong>: <a href="/symbol/mana/2r.svg">2 Colorless/Red SVG</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/mana/2r.svg<br>
			<br>
			The following mana codes are available:</p>
			{#manaCodes}
				<div class="symbol">{code}<br><div class="{className}">&nbsp;</div></div>
			{/manaCodes}
			<p>
			<br>
			You can also spell out the mana codes, such as 'green' for 'g', 'bluewhite' for 'uw', 'infinity' for 'âˆž', "halfwhite" for "hw", etc.<br>
			<br>
			You can also reverse any dual symbols, such as 'ru' for 'ur', 'r2' for '2r', etc.<br>
			</p>
		</div>
		<br>
		<br>
		<div class="code symbolsSection" id="otherSymbolsSection">
			<h2>Other Symbols</h2>
			<p><br>
			<strong>Format</strong>: http://mtgimage.com/symbol/other/&lt;code&gt;/&lt;size&gt;.&lt;format&gt;<br>
			<br>
			<strong>Examples</strong>:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/symbol/other/t/64.gif">Tap 64 GIF</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/other/t/64.gif</li>
				<li><a href="/symbol/other/q/128.png">Untap 128 PNG</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/other/q/128.png</li>
			</ul>
			<p><br>
			<strong>&nbsp;SVG Format</strong>: http://mtgimage.com/symbol/other/&lt;code&gt;.svg<br>
			<strong>SVG Example</strong>: <a href="/symbol/other/artifact.svg">Artifact SVG</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;http://mtgimage.com/symbol/other/artifact.svg<br>
			<br>
			The following codes are available:</p>
			{#otherCodes}
				<div class="symbol">{code}<br><div class="{className}">&nbsp;</div></div>
			{/otherCodes}
			<p>
			<br>
			You can also spell out some codes, such as 'tap' for 't' and 'untap' for 'q'.<br>
			<br>
			The card types (enchantment, instant, etc) come from Future Sight.<br>
			The power and toughness come from Portal.<br>
			The chaosdice and planeswalk come from Planechase.<br>
			</p>
		</div>
		<p>
		<br>
		All symbols are generated from the SVG files found here:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="http://www.mtgsalvation.com/forums/creativity/artwork/494438-baconcatbugs-set-and-mana-symbol-megapack">BaconCatBug's Set and Mana Symbol Megapack</a></li>
			<li><a href="http://www.slightlymagic.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=15&t=7010">Vector Set Symbols and Watermarks</a></li>
		</ul>
		<br>
		<br>
